english:
Of all paths, the Eightfold Path is supreme;
of all truths, the Four Noble Truths are supreme;
of all states, non-attachment is supreme;
of all two-legged beings, the Awakened One is supreme.

Heedfulness is the path to the deathless;
heedlessness is the path to death.
Those who are heedful do not die;
those who are heedless are already as the dead.

The bodhisattva was born for the sake of beings.
When beings are sick, the bodhisattva is sick;
when beings are healed, the bodhisattva is healed.

For one who clings, there is fear;
for one who does not cling,
there is no fear.

A flower spreads its fragrance without reserve;
a lamp shines its light without holding back.
The compassion of a bodhisattva is like this.

Karma follows like a shadow.
Plant good seeds and you harvest good;
plant evil seeds and you harvest evil.

Look at the world with the eyes of a child.
All things are new and wondrous;
each and every one is a miracle.

The middle way gives vision and knowledge;
it leads to calm, insight,
enlighenment, and nirvana.

Live each moment fully.
Do not linger on what has passed;
do not worry about what has not come.

The Eightfold Path is the best of paths;
the Four Truths are the best of truths.
Non-attachment is the best of states;
and the human being is the best of two-footed creatures.

Even in the heat of summer,
if the mind is cool,
one is already in a refreshing world.

Life-and-death and nirvana are not two;
affliction and enlightenment are not two.
This is the truth of non-duality.

This Dharma is equal;
there is no high or low.
That is why it is called supreme and perfect enlightenment.

Be a lamp unto yourself;
be a refuge unto yourself.
Make truth a lamp;
make truth a refuge.

In the Dharma there is a precious jewel;
may all beings be well by this truth.
In the Sangha there is a precious jewel;
may all beings be well by this truth.

O Shariputra,
form does not differ from emptiness;
emptiness does not differ from form.

The bodhisattva suffers the illness of beings together.
Only when beings are joyful is the bodhisattva joyful;
only when beings grieve does the bodhisattva grieve.

A straight mind is the bodhisattva's pure land;
a deep mind is the bodhisattva's pure land;
a compassionate mind is the bodhisattva's pure land.

For one without clinging,
there is no bondage;
for one with wisdom,
there is no delusion.
